12/03/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- The government met on Thursday (11 March) and approved the bill establishing a state minorities commission. 
The institution will be tasked with addressing the problems of minorities, working for protection of their human rights and helping them integrate into society. 
The commission will be subordinate to the prime minister. 
Along with the head of the commission, he will determine the number of members representing different minority groups in the country. 
(ATA - 11/03/04)
